{"id": "1431230940293894336", "channel_id": "1431230940293894336", "type": 0, "author_id": "212587018436345856", "author_name": "nactra", "author_bot": false, "content": "Unsure if this is a feature request or a QOL request, but i cannot find an option to have no awakener on the homescreen, only a background - does this option exist ? If it does, where is it ? Searched all menus and didn't find it. \nAnd if it doesn't, i would enjoy it", "timestamp": "2025-10-24T10:40:47.151000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1431230940293894336", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Keeping only the background on homescreen / no awakener", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1431076888939466782", "channel_id": "1431076888939466782", "type": 0, "author_id": "274743846061998080", "author_name": "swd7047", "author_bot": false, "content": "Dear Morimens Development Team,\n\nFirst of all, thank you sincerely for creating such a wonderful and inspiring game. I’m writing this message as a Korean player to share some feedback and suggestions that I hope may help improve the overall experience for many new players.\n\nSince yesterday, due to the influence of CZN, a large number of Korean users have joined the game and started their journey as new Keepers. However, since the game currently does not support a full Korean translation, immersion is significantly reduced. Despite this, many of us are still enjoying Morimens through auto-translated text as best we can.\n\nThat said, there are a few important issues we’ve noticed with the current Korean font in-game. The font size appears to be too large, causing lines of text to overlap or extend into a third line, which often makes dialogue unreadable (please see the attached images).\nWhile we understand that localization takes time, would it be possible to temporarily adjust the Korean font size in an upcoming patch? Ideally, the text could fit within two lines. This is not only a matter of immersion — during battles, it’s currently impossible to review dialogue or context when text is cut off, which makes it difficult to follow the story properly.", "timestamp": "2025-10-24T00:28:38.446000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1431076888939466782", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Suggestions from Korean Keepers", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
{"id": "1431076940177215569", "channel_id": "1431076888939466782", "type": 0, "author_id": "274743846061998080", "author_name": "swd7047", "author_bot": false, "content": "Secondly, regarding translation quality — we deeply appreciate the volunteer translators who are dedicating their time to help localize the game. However, since this process may take considerable time, we were wondering if the development team could help improve the quality of automatic translation.\nFor example, adding an optional Japanese → Korean GPT translation mode could greatly enhance readability, as Japanese and Korean share similar word order and sentence structure, which results in much more natural translation flow.\n\nI’ve been playing Morimens for about three months now and have spent quite a bit to support the game — not just as a player, but as a proud Keeper who truly loves this world. I sincerely wish for more people in Korea to experience the same joy and emotional impact that Morimens has given me.\n\nThanks to CZN’s influence, an incredible number of new Keepers have joined, many of whom have been deeply moved by the story and characters. I believe that the blessing of the Silver Key will also shine upon Korean Keepers soon.\n\nLastly, as a small personal wish — it would be wonderful if you could consider a rerun of Chapter 2 in November. The recently featured character Pickman was especially fun and charming, offering both exciting gameplay and strong performance. Many new players were eager to experience that event but unfortunately joined too late.\n\nThank you again for your hard work and dedication. I hope this feedback helps, and may the Silver Key guide the path of every member of the Morimens development team.\n\nSincerely,\nA Keeper from Korea 🕊️\n\n(Attachments included for reference)", "timestamp": "2025-10-24T00:28:50.662000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1431076888939466782", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Suggestions from Korean Keepers", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361168939622727801", "1361169005435420785"]}
